<div align="center">
<sub>004 — FEATURED BUILDS</sub>
</div>

<h2 align="center">Four things I'd actually show you</h2>

<br/>

<table width="100%">
<tr>
<td width="50%" valign="top">

<sub>01 / ANDROID</sub>

### Universal Download Manager

A download manager built for people who download a lot — resumable transfers, multi-source handling, and an interface that stays out of the way.

`Kotlin` · `Android` · <sub>**In active development**</sub>

</td>
<td width="50%" valign="top">

<sub>02 / PLATFORM</sub>

### Open Source Android App Store

A community-owned distribution alternative for Android apps — open, inspectable, and outside walled-garden gatekeeping.

`Kotlin` · `Open Source` · <sub>**Early stage**</sub>

</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="50%" valign="top">

<sub>03 / AI</sub>

### AI Productivity Suite

One assistant, four surfaces — communication, ideas, tasks, and motivation — built on modern LLM infrastructure instead of bolted-on chat.

`React` · `LLM tooling` · <sub>**In active development**</sub>

</td>
<td width="50%" valign="top">

<sub>04 / PWA</sub>

### Bangla Mess Manager

Shared-living logistics — rent, meals, expenses — modeled on how mess culture actually runs in Bangladesh, not a generic splitwise clone.

`PWA` · `JavaScript` · <sub>**Live**</sub>

</td>
</tr>
</table>

