<div align="center">
<sub>010 — OPEN SOURCE</sub>
</div>

<h2 align="center">Why give it away</h2>

<p align="center" width="600">
Because the tools I relied on to learn were free. Documentation, forums, other<br/>
people's repos — all of it was someone choosing to open the door behind them.<br/>
I build in the open for the same reason: not as a portfolio strategy, but because<br/>
that's how the field stays learnable for the next self-taught developer starting<br/>
from zero, the way I did.
</p>

